snippet.textDisplay: Ok so in my opinion, P.S. I Still Love You is a poor imitation of the book. The plot feels rushed and incomplete, and the characters underdeveloped. In the book, while Lara Jean does have hesitations about Peter, he doesn't act like as much of a douche as he does in the movie. In the book, I really wanted Peter and Lara to come out on top, even though JA was super adorkable. JA and Lara had super sweet moments in the book, and the snow scene was the cutest thing. All in all, throughout the movie, I was literally screaming at my screen for Lara to go off script and get with JA. The movie made Peter seem like an insensitive overprotective jerk wad, while JA was literally the perfect guy. Whatever, I'm pissed, and I can't imagine Always and Forever, Lara Jean will be that much worse.
